body:
Should solve a number of issues:
* Wire `c` is not detected as a primary output, and won't be made into a submod output port
```
module top(input a, output [1:0] b);
wire c;
(* submod="bar" *) sub s1(a, c);
assign b[0] = c;
endmodule
```
* Wire `b` is only partially used, but the entire bus will be made into a submodule output port, causing driver-driver conflict for `b[0]`:
```
module top(input a, output [1:0] b);
(* submod="bar" *) sub s1(a, b[1]);
assign b[0] = 1'b0;
endmodule
```
* `(* init = ... *)` is copied, not moved, into submodule causing `check -noinit` to give out warnings:
```
module top(input d, c, (* init = 1'b1 *) output reg q);
(* submod="bar" *) DFF s1(.D(d), .C(c), .Q(q));
endmodule

module DFF(input D, C, output Q);
parameter INIT = 1'b0;
endmodule
```
since top.q and top_bar.q would otherwise both have `(* init *)`

* Add `submod -hidden`:
```
    -hidden
        instead of creating submodule ports with public names, create ports with
        private names so that a subsequent 'flatten; clean' call will restore the
        original module with original public names.
```

code_blocks:
module top(input a, output [1:0] b);
wire c;
(* submod="bar" *) sub s1(a, c);
assign b[0] = c;
endmodule

module top(input a, output [1:0] b);
(* submod="bar" *) sub s1(a, b[1]);
assign b[0] = 1'b0;
endmodule

module top(input d, c, (* init = 1'b1 *) output reg q);
(* submod="bar" *) DFF s1(.D(d), .C(c), .Q(q));
endmodule

module DFF(input D, C, output Q);
parameter INIT = 1'b0;
endmodule
